m_q.target_metric: The name of the first building that held the title of tallest
filters: Buildings that were tallest at some point in time
sub_questions: Which buildings have valid 'Years as tallest' values?
What is the earliest year in the 'Years as tallest' column?
Which building corresponds to the earliest year as tallest?

scale_issues: Height ft (m) contains both feet and meters in a single string
Years as tallest contains year ranges (e.g., '1882–1886') and 'present' keyword

format_notes: Years as tallest column contains year ranges in format 'YYYY–YYYY' or 'YYYY–present'
Some rows have missing or dash values for Years as tallest (e.g., Nicollet Mall)
Height ft (m) column contains composite string with format 'feet (meters)'

constraints: Years as tallest must be parseable to extract start year
Rows with missing or dash values in Years as tallest should be excluded
The first building is determined by the earliest start year in Years as tallest
derived_filters: Filter out rows where Years as tallest is '-' or empty
Extract start year from Years as tallest range
output_format_requirements: Return the Name value of the building with the earliest start year
Output should be a single building name as a string
